Package: photomoss
Type: Package
Title: Calculates Spectral Indices for Multiple Areas per Photo
Version: 1.0
Date: 2018-04-18
Author: Manuel Molina with essential collaboration from Indradatta deCastro-Arrazola
Maintainer: Indradatta deCastro-Arrazola <indra@mncn.csic.es>
Authors@R: c(
    person("Indradatta", "deCastro-Arrazola", email = "indra@mncn.csic.es", role = c("aut", "cre")),
    person("Manuel", "Molina", email = "manuel.molbus@gmail.com", role = "aut"))

Description: Calculates spectral indices (NDVI...) for several areas of interest in multiple
    VIS (=VISible) and NIR (=Near InfraRed) pairs of photos. The package is 
    heavily based on package crustcover (available at GitHub username mosscoder).
License: GPL (>= 2)
Depends: raster
Imports: dplyr, rgeos, data.table, tiff, sp, RColorBrewer, spatstat, RImageJROI
BugReports: https://github.com/united-ecology/photomoss/issues
LazyData: true
